# Phase 1 Labs
- Navigate directories: `cd ~/ubuntu-linux-basics`, `ls -l`
- Create/remove directories: `mkdir test1`, `rmdir test1`
- Create/copy/move files: `touch file1`, `cp file1 file2`, `mv file2 file3`
- View files: `cat file3`, `less file3`, `head file3`, `tail file3`

# Phase 2 Labs
- Explore directories: `ls -l /etc`, `du -sh /var/*`
- Check disk usage: `df -h`
- Inspect files: `stat /etc/passwd`

# Phase 3 Labs
- Change permissions: `chmod 644 file.txt`, `chmod 755 script.sh`
- Change ownership: `sudo chown user file`, `chgrp group file`
- Test SUID/SGID/Sticky: `chmod u+s script.sh`, `chmod g+s script.sh`, `chmod +t /tmp/stickytest`

# Phase 4 Labs
- Add users/groups: `sudo useradd testuser`, `sudo groupadd testgroup`
- Assign user to group: `sudo usermod -aG testgroup testuser`
- Verify sticky bit on /tmp

# Phase 5 Labs
- Set ACL: `setfacl -m u:username:rw file.txt`
- Verify ACL: `getfacl file.txt`
- Test SUID/SGID scripts

# Phase 6 Labs
- Run background job: `sleep 60 &`
- Check jobs: `jobs`
- Bring job to foreground: `fg %1`
- Kill process: `kill -9 PID`

# Phase 7 Labs
- Check network interfaces: `ip a`
- Test connectivity: `ping google.com`
- Inspect sockets: `ss -tuln`
- Use dig/curl for DNS and HTTP requests

# Phase 8 Labs
- Update packages: `sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade`
- Install package: `sudo apt install tree`
- Remove package: `sudo apt remove tree`

# Phase 9 Labs
- Write script: `nano hello.sh` with `#!/bin/bash`, `echo "Hello"`
- Make executable: `chmod +x hello.sh`
- Run script: `./hello.sh`
- Loop exercise: for i in {1..5}; do echo $i; done

# Phase 10 Labs
- View logs: `tail -f /var/log/syslog`
- Backup config: `cp /etc/netplan/*.yaml ~/backups/`
- Create sample snapshot in VM
